Definition: conforming to accepted standards of social or professional behavior
Example: an ethical lawyer; ethical medical practice; an ethical problem; had no ethical objection to drinking; Ours is a world of nuclear giants and ethical infants- Omar N. Bradley
Synonyms: noun, motive, ethics, UNETHICAL, RIGHT, conforming, to, accepted, standards, of, social, or, professional, behavior, an, ethical, lawyer, medical, practice, problem, had, no, objection, drinking, Ours, is, a, world, nuclear, giants, and, infants, -, Omar, N, Bradley
Category: adj.all
